  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "+kTvYll2cb/4OT9YKxWmCqnx9m0=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\n\n**GSOC (Graffiti SOC)** is a many-to-one notification system that inverts the feed model \u2014 a shared mined private key lets multiple writers publish SOC updates that a single target node receives in real time.\n\n## Evidence\n\nMechanics:\n- A private key is mined so that its derived SOC address falls in the target node's neighborhood\n- Anyone with access to that private key can sign SOC updates\n- The target node subscribes via `WS /gsoc/subscribe/{address}` and receives updates as they arrive\n- Conceptually a \"mailbox\" anyone with the key can drop messages into\n\nComparison to feeds:\n\n|           | Feeds                 | GSOC                              |\n|-----------|-----------------------|-----------------------------------|\n| Writers   | Single (owner)        | Multiple (anyone with the key)    |\n| Readers   | Anyone                | Single target node                |\n| Direction | One-to-many broadcast | Many-to-one collection            |\n\nbee-js: `bee.gsocMine(targetOverlay, identifier, proximity?)`, `bee.gsocSend(stamp, signer, identifier, data)`, `bee.gsocSubscribe(address, identifier, handler)`.\n\n## Why it matters\n\nGSOC is the correct primitive for collaboration coordination: collaborators push notifications to a coordinator node without the coordinator needing to poll each participant's feed.\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
    }
  },
